	<article id="post-386" class="post-386 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-astronomy">
				<header class="entry-header">
			
						<h1 class="entry-title">From Dream To Reality</h1>
								</header><!-- .entry-header -->

				<div class="entry-content">
			<p><img src="../blogfiles/20091121/thumbs/cad-rendering.jpg" style="width:125px;height:113px;float:left;margin-right:10px;"></p>
<p>I have always been a pragmatic person. While designing my telescope using computer assisted design software was a very rewarding experience, I have felt a much greater sense of accomplishment making it happen. This is why I am very proud to show off the mirror box of my future telescope. This is the result of 4 nights of work at <a href="http://www.sawdustshop.com/">the sawdust shop</a> in Sunnyvale. I am very happy with the way it turned out, and look forward to getting more work done in the next few weeks! <strong>Note:</strong> click on the thumbnails below to see the full size photographs.</p>
<p><br style="clear:both;line-height:0;"/></p>
<p><a href="../blogfiles/20091121/IMG_2672.jpg" style="float:left;margin-right:10px;" target="_blank"><img src="../blogfiles/20091121/thumbs/IMG_2672.jpg" style="width:180px;height:135px;"></a></p>
<p><a href="../blogfiles/20091121/IMG_2673.jpg" style="float:left;margin-right:10px;" target="_blank"><img src="../blogfiles/20091121/thumbs/IMG_2673.jpg" style="width:180px;height:135px;"></a></p>
<p><a href="../blogfiles/20091121/IMG_2674.jpg" style="float:left;margin-right:10px;" target="_blank"><img src="../blogfiles/20091121/thumbs/IMG_2674.jpg" style="width:180px;height:135px;"></a></p>
<p><br style="clear:both;line-height:0;"/></p>
<p><a href="../blogfiles/20091121/IMG_2675.jpg" style="float:left;margin-right:10px;" target="_blank"><img src="../blogfiles/20091121/thumbs/IMG_2675.jpg" style="width:180px;height:135px;"></a></p>
